      "title": "Prove\n- Common input: (pp, [x]_2, [o]_1 = [1^n r]_1, [r_n]_1), [\\alpha_1]_1, [\\beta_1]_1.\n-\\mathcal{P} input: (\\mathsf{pp},[\\mathbf{r}]_1),\\mathbf{a_1},\\mathbf{b_1}.\n- Statement: [\\alpha_1]_1 = [\\mathbf{a_1}^\\top \\mathbf{r}] \\wedge [\\beta_1]_1 = [\\mathbf{b_1}^\\top \\mathbf{r}] \\wedge \\prod a_{1,i} = \\prod b_{1,i}.\n1. -\\mathcal{P} computes\n\\mathbf{a_2} = (1, a_1, a_1 a_2, \\dots, a_1 \\cdots a_{n-1}), \\quad \\mathbf{b_2} = (1, b_1, b_1 b_2, \\dots, b_1 \\cdots b_{n-1}),\na_3 = a_1 \\circ a_2, \\qquad b_3 = b_1 \\circ b_2.\nand respective commitments to them, [\\alpha_1]_1, [\\beta_1]_1, [\\alpha_2]_1, [\\beta_2]_1.\n- \\mathcal{P} \\text{ sends } [\\alpha_2]_1, [\\alpha_3]_1, [\\beta_2]_1 [\\beta_3]_1 \\text{ to } \\mathcal{V}.\n2. -\\mathcal{V} sends y and the prover and verifier sets w=y^n.\n- \\mathcal{V} computes the new key \\mathsf{ck}'_{\\mathcal{V}} \\leftarrow (y^{-2^0}[x_1]_2, \\dots, y^{-2^{\\nu-1}}[x_{\\nu}]_2).\n-\\mathcal{P} computes the new key \\mathsf{ck}_{\\mathcal{P}}' \\leftarrow [\\mathbf{r} \\circ \\mathbf{y}^{-\\mathbf{n}}]_1 and\nq(X) = a_1X + a_2X^{-1} + wb_1X^2 + b_2X^{-2} + a_3X^3 + b_3X^4\n\\mathbf{s}(X) = w^2 \\mathbf{v}^{\\mathbf{n}} X + w^3 \\mathbf{v}^{\\mathbf{n}} X^2\n+(-w^{2}y(\\mathbf{y^{n}}-y^{n-1}\\mathbf{e_{n}})+w^{4}\\mathbf{e_{n}}-\\mathbf{y^{n}})X^{-3}\n+ (-w^3y(\\mathbf{y^n} - y^{n-1}\\mathbf{e_n}) - w^4\\mathbf{e_n} - w\\mathbf{y^n})X^{-4}\nt(X) = \\mathbf{q}(X)^{\\top} (\\mathbf{q}(X) \\circ \\mathbf{y}^{\\mathbf{n}} + 2\\mathbf{s}(X)) - 2w^{2} - 2w^{3}.\nLet \\{t_i\\}_{i\\in\\{-6,8\\}\\setminus\\{0\\}} be the non-zero coefficients for t.\n\n- Prover computes \\{[\\tau_i]\\leftarrow t_i[1]\\}_{i\\in\\{-6,8\\}\\setminus\\{0\\}}.\n3. - Prover sends \\{[\\tau_i]\\}_{i \\in \\{-6,8\\} \\setminus \\{0\\}}.\n\n4. - \\mathcal{V} samples x \\leftarrow \\mathbb{Z}_q and sends it to the prover.\n-\\mathcal{P} computes \\mathbf{q}(x) and \\mathbf{q}(x) \\circ \\overline{\\mathbf{y}} + 2\\mathbf{s}(x). It also computes t_x \\leftarrow t(x).\n-\\mathcal{P} sends t_x.\n5.\n- \\mathcal{V} asserts that\nt_x[1] = \\sum_{i \\in \\{-6,8\\} \\setminus \\{0\\}} x^i[\\tau_i].\n- Let \\mathbf{s}(x) = a\\mathbf{y}^{\\mathbf{n}} + by^{n}\\mathbf{e}_{\\mathbf{n}}. \\mathcal{V} computes a, b and",
